The paper proposes a method to convert VQA into a machine reading comprehension problem by unifying all input information by natural language. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with complex interactions between different modalities, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper also mentions the exploration of large-scale external knowledge bases, which could be relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
